Phase 1: Infrastructure Setup and Provisioning

Learn: Docker/Podman basics, container networking, static IPs, SSH server setup in Ubuntu containers, SSH key authentication, and Ansible inventory basics.
Build: a compose.yml or docker-compose.yml / podman-compose.yml that starts 6 Ubuntu containers with SSH access, fixed IPs, and one network; then an Ansible inventory that can reach all 6 nodes. This phase also includes the first redis-tool provision flow that installs Redis 7.0.15, configures cluster mode, starts Redis, forms the cluster, and prints topology.

Phase 2: Data Seeding and Verification

Learn: deterministic data generation, Redis key distribution, redis-cli basics, and how to verify stored values programmatically.
Build: redis-tool data seed --keys 1000 to insert 1000 reproducible key-value pairs, and redis-tool data verify to read them back and confirm every value matches the expected result. The tool must also show a summary of inserted keys and any mismatches.

Phase 3: Cluster Status Reporting

Learn: Redis Cluster topology, roles, slot ranges, replica relationships, memory usage commands, and how to read cluster health state.
Build: redis-tool status that prints each node’s IP, port, role, Redis version, slot range for masters, replication target for replicas, cluster state, and memory usage in a clean readable format.

Phase 4: Rolling Upgrade

Learn: rolling upgrade strategy, failover handling, replica-first upgrade order, master promotion, cluster health checks, and zero-downtime maintenance.
Build: redis-tool upgrade --target-version 7.2.6 --strategy rolling that first checks cluster health, upgrades replicas one at a time, then upgrades masters using CLUSTER FAILOVER, and finally verifies data and version consistency. The cluster must remain healthy during the whole process.

Phase 5: Full Verification

Learn: post-upgrade validation, slot coverage checks, version consistency checks, replication lag checks, and cluster health auditing.
Build: redis-tool verify --full that confirms data integrity, same Redis version on all nodes, all 16384 hash slots covered, every master has a replica, cluster state is ok, and replicas are synced.